<item>
            <title>[PIG-2788] improved string interpolation of variables</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2788</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The simplest example of the failure of the current string interpolation is &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
store my_rel into &apos;$OUTPUT_&apos;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will raise an error saying that OUTPUT_ is not a variable passed in. Similar errors happen with a variety of other trailing characters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if &apos;$&lt;/p&gt;
{OUTPUT}
&lt;p&gt;_&apos;, or something similar, worked.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
